# Week 4
# 3. use of a transitive verb denoting an adverbial notion
Source: a:354
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {adverbs}
Igaedna            ti      agadal
i-gaed=na          ti      ag-adal
T-diligent=ERG.3SG CORE.SG I-study
`He studied diligently`

# Week 4
# 4. use of an adverb-like lexeme that does not require the ligature
# (ng)a when linking to a constituent. These words form a closed
# class and may also function as adjectives.
Source: a:355
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {adverbs}
Nagistayan ginetteb        ti      alingo    ti      tengngedna
Nagistayan getteb-{in}     ti      alingo    ti      tengnged=na
almost     tear.off-{PF.T} CORE.SG wild.boar CORE.SG neck=ERG.3SG
`The wild boar almost cut his neck`


