siak ti      paralako
1SG  CORE.SG paralako
'I am the salesperson'

# Week 4
# Independent pronoun and noun phrase to copula, number agreement mismatch
Source: a:33
Vetted: f
Judgment: f
Phenomena: {coordination agreement}
Siak dagiti  paralako
siak dagiti  paralako
1SG  CORE.PL paralako
'I am the salespersons'

# Week 4
# Coordination of pronoun and (proper) noun, to indicate the participation of
# an additional person. The enclitic pronoun apparently agrees with the pernum
# of all indicated participants (in this case, the speaker and another person,
# hence 1pEXCL)
Source: a:492
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {coordination agreement}
Napankami    ken Marta.
na-pan=kami  ken Marta
PF-go=1pEXCL and Marta
'Marta and I went.'

# Week 4
# Ungrammatical example as above, where the enclitic pronoun does NOT agree
# in number with the participants.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {coordination agreement}
Napan=ak  ken Marta.
na-pan=ak ken Marta.
PF-go=1sA ken Marta.
'Marta and I went.'

# Week 4
# Ken has a plural form, kada, used to coordinate plural nouns.
Source: a:493
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {coordination agreement}
dagiti  lallakay kada   babbaket
dagiti  lallakay kada   babbaket
CORE.PL old.men  and.PL old.women
'the old men and women (husbands and wives)'

# Week 4
# Ungrammatical use of singular "ken" with plural coordinates.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {coordination agreement}
dagiti  lallakay ken    babbaket
dagiti  lallakay ken    babbaket
CORE.PL old.men  and.SG old.women
'the old men and women'

