######################################
######### Embedded declaratives ######
######################################

# 1. "ta" complement clauses."Ta" complement clauses must be finite: 
# co-referential arguments are not deleted in the complement clause.
# To use "ta" with verbs, it is used with certain imperative verbs,
#  i.e. aguray `wait`, ibaga `tell`, umay `come`, etc

# week 4
# imperative + ta + declarative clause
Source: a:462
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {Embedded declaratives}
Aguraykayo     ta  sapulek
ag-uray=ka     ta  sapul-en=ko
I-wait=ABS.2SG SUB search-T=ERG.1SG
`Wait and I'll look for it`

# Week 4
# Ungrammatical example of 'ta' complement clause violating the constraint
# that such clauses must be finite. Coreferential argument in complement
# clause has been deleted.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {embedded declaratives}
Agsardengkan ta in aginanan.
ag-sardeng=ka=n ta  in ag-inana=n
I-stop=2sA=now  SUB go I-rest=now

# 2. In another case, complement clauses are preceded by Ligature, "(ng)a".
# Co-refential arguments may be expressed twice: once in the main clause,
# and again in the complement clause for clarity (to avoid any ambiguity.
# Week 4
Source: a:468
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {Embedded declaratives}
Ikariko           a   mapanak
i-kari=ko         a   ma-pan=ak
T-promise=ERG.1SG LIG I-go=ABS.1SG
`I promise to go (I promise that I go)`

# 3. (ng)a complements can accompany an impersonal predicate; these are
# clauses that do not take personal clitic pronouns or full noun phrase
# arguments along with their complement clauses.
Source: a:464
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {Embedded declaratives}
Nasken nga aginanakayo.
na-sekken nga ag-inana=kayo
ADJ-need  LIG I-rest=2pA
'It is necessary that you rest.'

# 4. There are (ng)a complements where NO arguments are specified, either in
# the predicate or the complement, as with meteorological verbs.
# Example of a (ng)a complement phrase with no specified arguments:
Source: a:464
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {embedded declaratives}
Mangrugi  nga agarbis.
mang-rugi nga ag-arbis
I-start   LIG I-drizzle

# Week 4
Source: a:242
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {Embedded declaratives}
Ammok        a   nakitamo         ti      lalaki
ammo=ko      a   na-kita=mo       ti      lalaki
know=ERG.1SG LIG PF.T-see=ERG.2SG CORE.SG boy
`I know that you saw the boy`


